    dc:creator "Fiege, Thomas Knebelsberger and Dieter", "Göưing, Miriam", "Meissner, Karin", "Schwentner, Martin" ;
    dc:date "2023" ;
    dc:title "Polychaetes distributed across oceans-examples of widely recorded species from abyssal depths of the Atlantic and Pacific Oceans" ;
    bibo:endPage "944" ;
    bibo:journal "Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society" ;
    bibo:startPage "906" ;
    bibo:volume "199" ;
    fabio:hasPart <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10470383>, <http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10470411> ;
    a fabio:JournalArticle .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10470383>
    dc:description "Figure 5. Geographic distribution and median-joining COI haplotype networks for Spiophanes spp.. The colour-code in the network corresponds to the geographic localities, each vertical linerepresents one mutational step and the size of each haplotype its frequency.Spiophanes adriaticus D’Alessandro etal., 2019from shallow waters of the Adriatic Sea is also displayed because sequence information deposited for this species suggest a close relationship to S. pacificus (which seems dubious).Haplotypes are numered 1–30, details are listed in the Supporting Information, Table S2. Dataavailable came from both the Atlantic and Pacific Oceans; type localities of S. longisetus and S. abyssalis are located in the North Atlantic Ocean, those of S.australis sp.nov.is in the Argentine Basin and of S. pacificus sp.nov.in the NW Pacific,each indicated by colour-coded asterisks." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10470383/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10470411>
    dc:description "Figure 18. Spiophanes cf. longisetus Meissner, 2005, LM and SEM studies: A, specimen stained with methyl green, dorsal view; note nuchal organ with associated yellow pigment, also note intensively stained glandular organs in middle chaetigers and distally stained neuropodium of chaetiger 8. B, anterior end until chaetiger 4, dorsal view; note dorsal nuchal organ extending to end of 2nd chaetiger. C, same in lateral view; note short stout cirriform occipital antenna with rounded tip.D, chaetigers 6–8, lateral view; note bacillary chaetae emerging from hole-like opening distally on chaetiger 8, also see enlarged detail below. E, leħ parapodia of chaetigers 7–9, stained with methyl green, lateral view; note intensively stained spot in 8th chaetiger. F, micrograph of quadridentate neuropodial hook from posterior chaetiger; note half-hood from the tip of the main fang to the shaħ.G, right parapodium of chaetiger 4, lateral view; note long sabre chaeta in inferior position. H, row of five neuropodial hooks of chaetiger 15 with sabre chaeta in inferior position (to the right in image). I, neuropodial quadridentate hook, lateral view; note half-hood from tip of main fang to shaħ.—A, ZMH-P 28154, MAR East; B, G, SMF 30641, MAR East; C, D, H, I, SMF 30640 (SEM stub 1327), MAR central; E, ZMH-P 28157, MAR East; F, ZMH-P 28155, MAR East.Scale Bars:A, 200 µm; B–D, F, 100 µm; E, 50µm; G, 20 µm; H, 10 µm; I, 5 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10470411/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

